label.value: anterior lateral line neuromast cupula development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the anterior lateral line neuromast cupula over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The cupula is secreted by mantle cells and the ciliary bundles of all of the hair cells of the neuromast are embedded in it. The cupula provides a mechanical linkage between the hair cells and the external hydrodynamic environment. The cupula of superficial neuromasts grows continuously, while the height of the cupula of canal neuromasts is limited by canal diameter.

label.value: anterior lateral line neuromast mantle cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an anterior lateral line neuromast mantle cell. Mantle cells are non-sensory cells that surround the sensory strip, separating the neuromast from the epidermis. Mantle cells secrete the cupula in which the ciliary bundles of all of the hair cells are embedded.

label.value: anterior lateral line neuromast support cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an anterior lateral line neuromast support cell. Support cells are non-sensory cells of the neuromast that extend between the sensory hair cells from the basement membrane to the apical surface; they are surrounded by mantle cells.

label.value: anterior lateral line ganglion development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the anterior lateral line ganglion over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The anterior lateral line ganglion develops from cranial ectodermal placodes situated between the eye and ear.

label.value: anterior lateral line ganglion neuron differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuron of the anterior lateral line ganglion.

label.value: anterior lateral line nerve development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the anterior lateral line nerve over time, form its formation to the mature structure. The anterior lateral line nerve contains efferent axons that innervate hair cells of the ALL and afferent axons that project to an octavolateralis column in the hindbrain. The octavolateralis column consists of the medial octavolateralis nucleus (MON), the caudal octavolateralis nucleus, and the magnocellular nucleus.

label.value: afferent axon development in anterior lateral line nerve

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an afferent axon in the anterior lateral line nerve over time from its formation to the mature structure. This process includes axonogenesis and pathfinding of the afferent axons in the anterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: efferent axon development in anterior lateral line nerve

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an efferent axon in the anterior lateral line nerve over time from its formation to the mature structure. This process includes axonogenesis and pathfinding of the efferent axons in the anterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: glial cell migration in anterior lateral line nerve

value.value: The movement of a glial cell along the axons in the anterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: anterior lateral line nerve glial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a glial cell in the anterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: myelination of anterior lateral line nerve axons

value.value: The formation of compact myelin sheaths around the axons of the anterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: posterior lateral line system development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the posterior lateral line system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The posterior lateral line system develops from cranial ectodermal placodes, situated behind the ear, that give rise to both the neuromasts and the posterior lateral line sensory nerves that innervate the neuromasts. The posterior lateral line system consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head of all fishes and most amphibians. The neuromasts are innervated by several lateral line nerves, which project primarily to the hindbrain. The posterior mechanosensory lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance.

label.value: posterior lateral line development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the posterior lateral line over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The posterior lateral line consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the body and trunk of all fishes and most amphibians. The posterior lateral line develops from cranial ectodermal placodes situated behind the ear.

label.value: posterior lateral line ganglion development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the posterior lateral line ganglion over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The posterior lateral line ganglion develops from cranial ectodermal placodes situated behind the ear.

label.value: posterior lateral line nerve development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the posterior lateral line nerve over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The posterior lateral line nerve innervates hair cells of the PLL and projects to an octavolateralis column in the hindbrain that consists of the medial octavolateralis nucleus (MON), the caudal octavolateralis nucleus, and the magnocellular nucleus.

label.value: posterior lateral line neuromast development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the posterior lateral line neuromast over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The neuromast is the sensory receptor of the anterior lateral line system and is composed of a population of sensory hair cells, and nonsensory supporting cells and mantle cells. Neuromast are located superficially on the epithelium or in lateral line canals.

label.value: posterior lateral line neuromast primordium migration

value.value: The migration of a relatively undifferentiated cell along the developing posterior lateral line, originating from cranial ectodermal placodes situated behind the ear. The neuromast primordium deposits proneuromasts along the lateral line, from which the neuromasts will develop.

label.value: posterior lateral line neuromast cupula development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the posterior lateral line neuromast cupula over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The cupula is secreted by mantle cells and the ciliary bundles of all of the hair cells of the neuromast are embedded in it. The cupula provides a mechanical linkage between the hair cells and the external hydrodynamic environment. The cupula of superficial neuromasts grows continuously, while the height of the cupula of canal neuromasts is limited by canal diameter.

label.value: posterior lateral line neuromast deposition

value.value: The process in which a migrating neuromast primordium deposits clusters of undifferentiated cells (proneuromasts) along its migratory path in the developing posterior lateral line.

label.value: posterior lateral line neuromast hair cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a posterior lateral line neuromast hair cell. (N.B. This may be development of neuromast hair cell type or a set of cell of neuromast hair cell type. This will involve the change of a cell or set of cells from one cell identity to another). Hair cells are the sensory receptors of the neuromast and are located in a portion of the neuromast called the sensory strip. Each hair cell of the neuromast is morphologically polarized as a result of the relative position of the single kinocilium and the clusters of stereocilia on its apical surface. There are approximately seven hair cells within each neuromast, with each hair cell innervated by afferent and efferent neurons.

label.value: posterior lateral line neuromast mantle cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a posterior lateral line neuromast mantle cell. (N.B. This may be development of neuromast mantle cell type or a set of cells of neuromast mantle cell type. This will involve the change of a cell or set of cells from one cell identity to another). Mantle cells are non-sensory cells that surround the sensory strip, separating the neuromast from the epidermis. Mantle cells secrete the cupula in which the ciliary bundles of all of the hair cells are embedded.

label.value: lateral line system development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the lateral line system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The lateral line system is a network of sensory organs (neuromasts) and lateral line nerves located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head and body of all fishes and most amphibians. The lateral line system develops from cranial ectodermal placodes situated between the eye and ear.

label.value: electrosensory lateral line system development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the electrosensory lateral line system over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: posterior lateral line neuromast support cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a posterior lateral line neuromast support cell. Support cells are non-sensory cells of the neuromast that extend between the sensory hair cells from the basement membrane to the apical surface; they are surrounded by mantle cells.

label.value: posterior lateral line ganglion neuron differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuron of the posterior lateral line ganglion.

label.value: efferent axon development in posterior lateral line nerve

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an efferent axon in the posterior lateral line nerve over time from its formation to the mature structure. This process includes axonogenesis and pathfinding of the efferent axons in the posterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: glial cell migration in posterior lateral line nerve

value.value: The movement of a glial cell along the axons in the posterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: posterior lateral line nerve glial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a glial cell in the posterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: myelination of posterior lateral line nerve axons

value.value: The formation of compact myelin sheaths around the axons of the posterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: afferent axon development in posterior lateral line nerve

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an afferent axon in the posterior lateral line nerve over time from its formation to the mature structure. This process includes axonogenesis and pathfinding of the afferent axons in the posterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: peripheral nervous system neuron differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuron whose cell body resides in the peripheral nervous system.

label.value: peripheral nervous system neuron development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron whose cell body is located in the peripheral nervous system, from initial commitment of the cell to a neuronal fate, to the fully functional differentiated neuron.

label.value: peripheral nervous system neuron axonogenesis

value.value: Generation of a long process from a neuron whose cell body resides in the peripheral nervous system. The axon carries action potential from the cell body towards target cells.

label.value: lateral line nerve glial cell development

value.value: The process aimed at the progression of a lateral line glial cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label.value: lateral line nerve glial cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation

value.value: The process in which the structure of a glial cell in a lateral line nerve is generated and organized. This process occurs while the initially relatively unspecialized cell is acquiring the specialized features of a glial cell in a lateral line nerve.

label.value: anterior lateral line nerve glial cell development

value.value: The process aimed at the progression of a glial cell in the anterior lateral line nerve over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label.value: anterior lateral line nerve glial cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation

value.value: The process in which the structures of a glial cell in the anterior lateral line nerve are generated and organized. This process occurs while the initially relatively unspecialized cell is acquiring the specialized features of a glial cell in the anterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: posterior lateral line nerve glial cell development

value.value: The process aimed at the progression of a glial cell in the posterior lateral line nerve over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label.value: posterior lateral line nerve glial cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation

value.value: The process in which the structures of a glial cell in the posterior lateral line nerve are generated and organized. This process occurs while the initially relatively unspecialized cell is acquiring the specialized features of a glial cell in the posterior lateral line nerve.

label.value: chromosome localization

value.value: Any process in which a chromosome is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label.value: D-glutaminase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + L-glutamine = NH3 + D-glutamate.

label.value: D-proline reductase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: 5-aminopentanoate + [PrdC protein]-Se-L-selenocysteinyl-S-L-cysteine = [PrdC protein]-L-selenocysteine/L-cysteine + D-proline.

label.value: deoxycytidylate C-methyltransferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: 5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate + dCMP = 2'-deoxy-5-methyl-5'-cytidylate + 7,8-dihydrofolate.

label.value: isoflavone 7-O-glucosyltransferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose + isoflavone = UDP + isoflavone 7-O-beta-D-glucoside.

label.value: isohexenylglutaconyl-CoA hydratase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-hydroxy-3-(4-methylpent-3-en-1-yl)glutaryl-CoA = 3-(4-methylpent-3-en-1-yl)pent-2-enedioyl-CoA + H2O.

label.value: isomaltulose synthase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: sucrose = 6-O-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl-D-fructofuranose.

label.value: isonocardicin synthase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine(1+) + nocardicin E = S-methyl-5'-thioadenosine + H+ + isonocardicin A.

label.value: isopiperitenone delta-isomerase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: isopiperitenone = piperitenone.

label.value: isopropanol dehydrogenase (NADP+) activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: NADP+ + propan-2-ol = acetone + H+ + NADPH.

label.value: isovitexin beta-glucosyltransferase activity

value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: isovitexin + UDP-D-glucose = H+ + isovitexin 2''-O-beta-D-glucoside + UDP.
